replies.bodyText:
I did not make this change. Upon further investigation I don't think this change is feasible due to a reflection restriction involving classloading.  Within TestServletProcessor we can remove the build dependencies on classes <platform>.servlet.http.HttpServlet, but not on classes <platform>.servlet.annotation.WebServlet.  The getQueryPaths() method computes the servlet query path from the value and urlPatterns methods (attributes) of the WebServlet annotation.  It's possible to invoke these methods using reflection, but in the FAT runtime the following pattern fails with an exception indicating the object is not an instance of declaring class, which means the method (m) and the target class (webServletClass) are not loaded by the same classloader. I don't see how to alleviate the restriction.
`Class<? extends Annotation> webServletClass =
Class.forName("platform.servlet.annotation.WebServlet");
Annotation webServlet = anno.servlet().getAnnotation(webServletClass);
Method m = webServletClass.getDeclaredMethod("value");
String[] webServletValue = (String[]) m.invoke(webServletClass, (Object[]) null);`

